I"<p>This is a beginner-friendly tutorial based on <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/github/working-with-github-pages/testing-your-github-pages-site-locally-with-jekyll">Testing your GitHub Pages site locally with Jekyll</a>
on <a href="https://docs.github.com/en">GitHub Docs</a>.</p>

<p>Before you start:</p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>You need to have a GitHub Pages site with Jekyll. Here is a tutorial on <a href="http://jmcglone.com/guides/github-pages/">how to create and host GitHub Pages site</a>,</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Have a Windows 10 PC and have WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux) installed. Here is a tutorial on <a href="https://www.windowscentral.com/install-windows-subsystem-linux-windows-10">How to install WSL on Windows 10</a>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Have your publishing source for your site cloned to your PC. Read more about <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/github/working-with-github-pages/about-github-pages#publishing-sources-for-github-pages-sites">Publishing sources for GitHub Pages sites</a> 
and</p>
  </li>
</ol>

